<span id="freeTextContainer7696885875842991415">My Review - The Penance List by S.C. Cunningham<br/><br/>Oh my goodness! The Penance List is so fast-paced, I fell off the bed reading it! I have to admit it is not my usual cup of tea and I don&apos;t really like blood and guts. But this was well written and had tempo so you don&apos;t dwell on the &quot;gore bits&quot;. <br/><br/>The Good<br/>Great style, lots of action and intrigue. What a change from romance and I honestly do think that I could fall in love with this genre. I am glad I took a chance on it. <br/><br/>The Bad<br/>Somethings put me off </span>
  <span id="freeText7696885875842991415" style="display:none">My Review - The Penance List by S.C. Cunningham<br /><br />Oh my goodness! The Penance List is so fast-paced, I fell off the bed reading it! I have to admit it is not my usual cup of tea and I don't really like blood and guts. But this was well written and had tempo so you don't dwell on the "gore bits". <br /><br />The Good<br />Great style, lots of action and intrigue. What a change from romance and I honestly do think that I could fall in love with this genre. I am glad I took a chance on it. <br /><br />The Bad<br />Somethings put me off my dinner... but I am pretty sure that is the genre and the author wanted that!!<br /><br />The Ugly<br />There was so much in this book; I realized I am a little old mumsy type! (Can often be confused with an old fart!) But that doesn't mean the book was ugly. I don't know how, but I enjoyed it!<br /><br />A great read! 5 Stars... Dare I say, I want more?!!!<br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
