<div id="review_651560951" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/651560951" />
    <a title="Krissy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11310147-krissy"><img alt="Krissy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1405202315p2/11310147.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/651560951?book_show_action=true">Jun 26, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Krissy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Krissy" href="/user/show/11310147-krissy">Krissy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer651560951" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7626932515426769755">Well, I finished reading this last night, but needed a good nights sleep before writing a review because it completely mind f**ked me. <br/>I want to make it clear that is was absolutely NOT a romance novel. I knew that before I started reading it, but had no clue as to how deranged it was going to be. It&apos;s exactly what a was looking for. <br/>It gave me the same gross feelings that captive in the dark did. I was like &quot;What!! Whoa!! Ugh!! Eek!!&quot; Then was all &quot;lol!!&quot; <br/>All of the characters were so well deve</span>
  <span id="freeText7626932515426769755" style="display:none">Well, I finished reading this last night, but needed a good nights sleep before writing a review because it completely mind f**ked me. <br />I want to make it clear that is was absolutely NOT a romance novel. I knew that before I started reading it, but had no clue as to how deranged it was going to be. It's exactly what a was looking for. <br />It gave me the same gross feelings that captive in the dark did. I was like "What!! Whoa!! Ugh!! Eek!!" Then was all "lol!!" <br />All of the characters were so well developed and well needed. Their lives were all intertwined with each others and equally dysfunctional. <br />This story was SO suspenseful and contained lots of graphic and mature subjects such as: murder, rape, voyeurism, drugs, prostitution, stalking, BDSM and lots of sex! Hot sex, not so hot sex, straight sex and gay sex. <br />This book made me feel so many different emotions. Each character had their own story and I got wrapped up in each one! I loved some of the terms used that I'm not used to reading And had a lot of laugh out loud moments at some of the things said. <br />I still can't wrap my mind around some of the madness, but I enjoyed this book thoroughly. I literally could not put it down! </span>
  <a data-text-id="7626932515426769755" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


