nds can relax, broken David is dead. Laughter soon turns to fear when he communicates via Tara\'s laptop that he is very much alive, knows their every move and is ready to finish what he started. He is among them, but who, he has a brand new face? Tara is ready for him. There is nothing more dangerous that a woman unafraid of death... Come out, come out, wherever you are... SIOBHAN C CUNNINGHAM British Author of The David Trilogy (Thriller) and The Fallen Angel Series (Paranormal Romance) creates psychological twists and turns with a skilled mix of fueled tension, dark humor and pulsating sex scenes. Her colorful life offers her works a fresh level of sincerity and authority rare in fiction. CUNNINGHAM WRITES WHAT SHE KNOWS Having crossed paths with a violent serial attacker, her journey sparked the fuse for the riveting David Trilogy. As a child she was taken and survived, another little girl didn\'t, thus sowing the seed for her ball-breaking Fallen Angel Series. An ex-model, British born of Irish roots, she married a rock musician and has worked in the exciting worlds of music, film, sports, celebrity management and as a Police Crime Investigator (Wanted &amp; Absconder Unit, Intelligence Analyst, Major Crime Team, Investigations Hub). &quot;Gripping Story - I admire this author, she isn\'t afraid to push the boundaries.&quot; &quot;Explosive and visceral... compelling.&quot; &quot;Holy Shit is all I can say!!! These books are going to make AMAZING films!!!&quot; &quot;Cunningham has done it again! What a fantastic writer. The second book in the series is just as brilliant as the first,&quot; &quot;Pick it up when you have plenty of time because you won\'t want to put it down.&quot; &quot;It keeps you on edge not knowing what is going to happen next.&quot; &quot;Had me reading and reading to the small hours. Gripping! Can\'t wait for the third in the series.&quot; \'OMG!! Finished \'Unfinished business\'! You certainly know how to have an ending AGAIN.&quot; &quot;I raise a glass, I\'d love to meet anyone who writes like this.&quot; &quot;Blown away to the point of speechless. Shocking, vivid and bloody well written!!&quot; &quot;A talented writer, I was compelled to keep reading and now I\'m frustrated because I WANT MORE!&quot; &quot;Wow this is powerful and vivid. It is nice to see someone writing in the thriller/romance genre.&quot; &quot;A hard-hitting, forceful narrative that is about as powerful as anything I\'ve seen.&quot; &quot; ...writing doesn\'t get much better than this.&quot; &quot;Can\'t wait for the film to be released and book 3!&quot; &quot;Masterful, dark and suspenseful, you expertly exploit tensions between the erotic and the macabre, your characterisation of David is phenomenal.&quot; &quot;Truly amazing book. Highly recommend it.&quot; &quot;Thoroughly entertaining, a mind-bending instant classic.&quot; &quot;I love what you\'ve done: you\'ve somehow given us all the things we want to read about in one.&quot; &quot;I read the book in one sitting.&quot; \'Cunningham has crafted an epic in proportion novel here. Her characters are sultry and as real as they can get.&quot; &quot;I found myself snatching it up every chance I could, wanting to see what David would do next.&quot; &quot;Be on the lookout for more from this immensely talented rising literary star.&quot; &quot;\'Have to say the book is fabulous ... genuinely brilliant!&quot; &quot;I just love it, can\'t put it down. I really like the way you write.&quot; &quot;Unfinished Business is every bit as good as The Penance List. You did not disappoint.<\/span>\n  <a data-text-id=\"17049163191481297523\" href=\"#\" onclick=\"swapContent(\$(this));; return false;\">...more<\/a>\n\n    <\/div>\n\n      <div class=\'wtrButtonContainer wtrSignedOut\' id=\'26_book_34431020\'>\n<div class=\'wtrUp wtrLeft\'>\n<form action=\"/shelf/add_to_shelf\" accept-charset=\"UTF-8\" method=\"post\"><input name=\"utf8\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"&#x2713;\" /><input type=\"h